Numbered Discourses 7 
9. An Ascetic 
92. A Perfected One 
“Mendicants, it’s by being far from seven things that you become a perfected one. 
What seven? 
Identity view, doubt, misapprehension of precepts and observances, greed, hate, delusion, and conceit. 
It’s because of being far from these seven things that you become a perfected one.” 
